---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About" description="Justin Helmer — Principal Engineer.">
  <div class="page-header">
    <h1 class="page-heading">About</h1>
  </div>
  <div class="about-text">
    <p>I started in design. Then JavaScript. Then servers, then systems, then scale. Seventeen years in, I've touched every layer of the stack and I'm still just as curious about how things work underneath as I was on day one.</p>
    <p>Right now I'm building AI infrastructure — the kind of systems that need to be fast, composable, and resilient enough to run at global scale. Before that I built mobile platforms, real-time services, permissioning systems, developer tools. The through-line is always the same: make complex things simple so other people can build on top of them.</p>
    <p>I care less about what language or framework and more about whether the abstractions hold up under pressure. Good systems disappear. You stop thinking about them because they just work.</p>
    <p>The next generation of builders won't all be engineers. They'll be anyone with desire and drive. I'm helping build the systems that will support them.</p>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .about-text {
    max-width: 560px;
    font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .about-text p + p {
    margin-top: 1.5em;
  }
</style>
